official_title: To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to repeal the employer health insurance mandate.

summary.text: American Job Protection Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to repeal provisions added by the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act requiring certain employers who have a workforce of 50 or more full-time employees to provide health insurance coverage for their employees.

titles.title: To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to repeal the employer health insurance mandate.
